short_bio: Jenny Smith is a classically trained chef who specializes in French cuisine. She worked at several Michelin-starred restaurants in Paris before moving to New York to open her own restaurant.
Juan Rodriguez is a Mexican chef who draws inspiration from his mother's cooking. He has worked at several high-end restaurants in Mexico City and now owns a popular taqueria in Los Angeles.
Emily Chen is a Chinese-American chef who specializes in fusion cuisine. She has worked in some of the top restaurants in San Francisco and now runs her own pop-up restaurant.
Mohammed Ali is an Egyptian chef who is passionate about Middle Eastern cuisine. He has worked at several restaurants in Cairo and now owns a popular Middle Eastern restaurant in London.
Grace Kim is a Korean-American chef who specializes in Korean fusion cuisine. She has worked at some of the top restaurants in Los Angeles and now runs her own food truck.
Carlos Gonzalez is a Mexican chef who specializes in regional cuisine from Oaxaca. He has worked at several top restaurants in Mexico and now owns a popular Mexican restaurant in Chicago.
Anna Lee is a Korean chef who is passionate about traditional Korean cuisine. She has worked at some of the top restaurants in Seoul and now owns a popular Korean restaurant in New York City.
Luca Rossi is an Italian chef who specializes in Tuscan cuisine. He has worked at several top restaurants in Florence and now owns a popular Italian restaurant in San Francisco.
Maggie Chen is a Chinese chef who is passionate about Sichuan cuisine. She has worked at some of the top restaurants in Chengdu and now owns a popular Sichuan restaurant in Vancouver.
